  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex transactions or legitimate businesses. Key legal elements typically include:\n\n1. Three core stages:\n- Placement (introducing illegal funds into financial system)\n- Layering (concealing the source through complex transactions)\n- Integration (making funds appear legitimate)\n\n2. Common legal components:\n- Knowingly conducting financial transactions with proceeds from illegal activity\n- Attempting to conceal the source of illegally obtained funds\n- Engaging in transactions designed to disguise the origin of criminal proceeds\n\n3. Jurisdictional variations exist, but most definitions require:\n- Intentional action\n- Knowledge of funds' criminal origin\n- Deliberate attempt to disguise or legitimize illegal income\n\nFor precise details, I recommend consulting specific legal statutes in your jurisdiction, as definitions can vary between countries and legal systems.",
